Calculation and visualization of $\Delta$ d/d and $\Delta \Psi$¶

  • 4-inch data
  • Calculate d/d $\psi$=0, $\psi$=120, $\psi$=-120
  • Take the difference from the neighboring pixel

Calculation results

  • |d/d| = 2e-4/1.006 = 1.988e-04 < 2.18e-4
  • || < p/L = 1.0 104rad (=0.0057)
  • The measurement data is below the measurement limit.

limitation principle¶

|d/d| < (/) - (pcot(B)/(2Lsin(2B)))

  • L=0.5 m
  • /= 2.8 104
  • p= 50 m
  • Another limitation about the local lattice-plane curvature || arises from the geometrical consideration on a plane perpendicular to the diffraction plane.
  • || < p/L.
  • || is smallerthan 1.0104rad (=0.0057) for L=0.5 m.

experimental conditions for 4 inch data¶

  • p = 0.05 mm
  • L = 500 mm
  • GaN (1124) d = 1.006
  • = 1.284
  • incident angle: 0.58
  • Bragg angle(B) : 39.66
  • 2B: 79.3
